The paper deals with learning in spiking neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on spatiotemporal encoding, which suggests that it may be related to computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a new supervised learning rule, which suggests that it may be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the encoding of information in the nervous system, which suggests that it may be related to computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
